    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/ TRACTION CONTROL TROUBLESHOOTING: BENDIX - 9100, 9200, 9300 and 9400 Models Built March 1,
        1998 and After - TROUBLESHOOTING - TESTING TRACTION ACTIVE LIGHT (ON INSTRUMENT PANEL)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="test" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TESTING TRACTION ACTIVE LIGHT (ON INSTRUMENT PANEL)</title>
        <table id="t0404220" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Traction Active Light (On Instrument Panel)</title>
            <tgroup cols="6" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.93in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="1.21in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" colwidth="1.68in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="6" spanname="s1t6" align="center"/>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="6" spanname="s1t6">
                            <para>Perform
                                <emph type="bold">
                                    <hotlnk document="s04042_25.xml" xrefid="t0404219">TESTING TRACTION CONTROL ON/OFF
                                        SWITCH
                                        <xref refid="t0404219"/>
                                    </hotlnk>
                                </emph>
                                before performing this test.
                                <emph type="bold">NOTE: Check Traction Active bulb for open filament before performing
                                    this test.
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>STEP</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>KEY</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>ACTION</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>YES / IN SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>NO / OUT OF SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>The Traction Active Light and the ABS Warning Light share the same feed as the other
                                lights in the gauge cluster. If both lights do not work, check 10A fuse F4-A.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Fuse OK.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At back of cluster connector (420), jumper circuit 94BD to ground and note if Traction
                                Active Light is ON.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Light ON.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Check bulb. If bulb is good, replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (355) from controller. Turn Key ON and at (355), use test lead to
                                jumper terminal C2 (Orange wire) to ground. Note if Traction Active Light is ON.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Light ON.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Connect (355) to controller. Run
                                <hotlnk document="s04042_7.xml" xrefid="t0404201">INITIAL START-UP TEST PROCEDURE
                                    <xref refid="t0404201"/>
                                </hotlnk>
                                and note if Traction Active Light illuminates for bulb test. If not replace the
                                controller.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Locate open in circuit between connector (420) terminal 14 and connector (355)
                                terminal C2, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
